[{"location":"goesr_example/#Reading-and-Plotting-GOES-R-XRS-Data","page":"GOES-R XRS Example","title":"Reading and Plotting GOES-R XRS Data","text":"Example for reading and plotting GOES-R EXIS X-ray sensor data","category":"section"},{"location":"goesr_example/#Basic-Usage","page":"GOES-R XRS Example","title":"Basic Usage","text":"using SpaceWeather\nusing Dates\n\n# Download and load XRS data for a single day\ndata = goesr_xrs(16, Date(2020, 6, 1))\n\n# Access X-ray flux data\nxrsa = data.xrsa_flux  # Short wavelength (0.05-0.4 nm)\nxrsb = data.xrsb_flux  # Long wavelength (0.1-0.8 nm)\n\n# Access timestamps\ntimes = data.time","category":"section"},{"location":"goesr_example/#Plotting-Example","page":"GOES-R XRS Example","title":"Plotting Example","text":"using CairoMakie\n\naxis = (;\n    yscale = log10,\n    xlabel = \"Time (UTC)\",\n    ylabel = \"X-Ray Flux (W/mÂ²)\",\n)\nfap = plot(\n    data.time, data.xrsa_flux;\n    label = \"GOES-16 XRS-A (0.05-0.4 nm)\",\n    color = :mediumorchid,\n    axis = axis\n)\n\nplot!(\n    data.time, identity.(data.xrsb_flux),\n    label = \"GOES-16 XRS-B (0.1-0.8 nm)\",\n    color = :green,\n)\nfap","category":"section"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather","text":"Documentation for SpaceWeather.\n\nSpaceWeather.jl provides easy access to space weather indices and data, with automatic downloading and caching from various sources.","category":"section"},{"location":"#Installation","page":"Home","title":"Installation","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"SpaceWeather\")","category":"section"},{"location":"#Quickstart","page":"Home","title":"Quickstart","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Basic-Usage","page":"Home","title":"Basic Usage","text":"using SpaceWeather\nusing Dates\n\n# Fetch all available space weather data from Celestrak\ndata = celestrak()\n\n# Access Kp index (3-hourly planetary K-index)\nkp_values = data.Kp                              # All Kp values as KeyedArray\nkp_at_time = data.Kp(DateTime(2023, 1, 1, 1, 30))  # Query specific time\n\n# Access Ap index (3-hourly planetary A-index)\nap_values = data.Ap\n\n# Get data for a specific time range\ndata_2023 = celestrak(Date(2023, 1, 1), Date(2023, 12, 31))\nkp_2023 = data_2023.Kp\nap_2023 = data_2023.Ap\n\n# High-level accessor functions\nkp = Kp(Date(2023, 1, 1), Date(2023, 12, 31))\nap = Ap(Date(2023, 1, 1), Date(2023, 12, 31))\n\nData is automatically cached and can be refreshed with celestrak(update=true). Cache is automatically refreshed if older than 30 days.","category":"section"},{"location":"#API-Reference","page":"Home","title":"API Reference","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather.Celestrak","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather.Celestrak","text":"Celestrak space weather data.\n\nSource: https://celestrak.com/SpaceData/\nDocumentation: https://celestrak.org/SpaceData/SpaceWx-format.php\n\nProvides:\n\ndata.Kp: KeyedArray vector of 3-hourly Kp values indexed by timestamps\ndata.Ap: KeyedArray vector of 3-hourly Ap values indexed by timestamps\nAll CSV columns: data.DATE, data.ISN, data.F10_7_OBS, etc.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather.GoesrXrs","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather.GoesrXrs","text":"GOES-R EXIS X-Ray Sensor (XRS) data.\n\nSource: https://data.ngdc.noaa.gov/platforms/solar-space-observing-satellites/goes/\nDocumentation: https://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/stp/satellite/goes-r.html\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather.Ap-Tuple","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather.Ap","text":"Ap(args...; source=:celestrak, kwargs...)\n\nGet Ap index data from source.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather.Kp-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather.Kp","text":"Kp(t0, t1; source=:celestrak, kwargs...)\n\nGet Planetary K-index data from source.\n\nhttps://www.swpc.noaa.gov/products/planetary-k-index\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather.celestrak-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather.celestrak","text":"celestrak(t0, t1; update=false) :: Celestrak\n\nLoad and filter Celestrak data between dates t0 and t1 (inclusive).\n\nExample\n\n# Get data for year 2023\ndata_2023 = celestrak(Date(2023,1,1), Date(2023,12,31))\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather.celestrak-Tuple{}","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather.celestrak","text":"celestrak(; update=false) :: Celestrak\n\nLoad daily space weather data from Celestrak.\n\nSet update=true to refresh data from the server.\n\nExample\n\ndata = celestrak()\ndata.Kp                           # KeyedArray with 3h timestamps\ndata.Kp(DateTime(2023,1,1,1,30))  # Access by timestamp\ndata.KP1                          # First 3h interval (daily)\ndata.ISN                          # Sunspot numbers\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather.datadir-Tuple{}","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather.datadir","text":"datadir()\n\nReturn the default data directory for cached space weather files.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather.download_file-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather.download_file","text":"download_file(url, dest; update=false, min_age=Hour(3))\n\nDownload a file from url to dest if it doesn't exist or is older than min_age.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather.goesr_xrs-Tuple{Any, Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather.goesr_xrs","text":"goesr_xrs(id, t0::Date, t1::Date; update=false) :: GoesrXrs\n\nLoad GOES-R XRS data for a date range, combining multiple daily files.\n\nExample\n\ndata = goesr_xrs(16, Date(2020, 6, 1), Date(2020, 6, 2))\ndata.xrsa_flux  # Combined X-ray flux data\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather.goesr_xrs-Tuple{Any, Any}","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather.goesr_xrs","text":"goesr_xrs(id, time; update=false) :: GoesrXrs\n\nDownload and load GOES-R XRS data for a specific id and time.\n\nExample\n\ndata = goesr_xrs(16, Date(2020, 6, 1))\ndata.xrsa_flux  # Short wavelength X-ray flux\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather.xrsa-Tuple{Any, Vararg{Any}}","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather.xrsa","text":"xrsa(id, args...; kwargs...)\n\nGet GOES-R XRS-A (0.05-0.4 nm) X-ray flux data.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#SpaceWeather.xrsb-Tuple{Any, Vararg{Any}}","page":"Home","title":"SpaceWeather.xrsb","text":"xrsb(id, args...; kwargs...)\n\nGet GOES-R XRS-B (0.1-0.8 nm) X-ray flux data.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
